sentences.english: A user may decide to consider stamps older than a certain age invalid.
sentences.chinese: 用戶可能會決定認爲比特定期限更早的戳記是非法的。
首先，戳記攜帶一個日期。

sentences.english: The resource for which a stamp is minted.
sentences.chinese: 戳記爲哪個資源而生成。

sentences.english: The number of leading zeros discovered is the bit value of a particular stamp.
sentences.chinese: 所找到的前導零的數目就是特定戳記的比特值。

sentences.english: Checking a stamp, of course, takes a tiny fraction of a second.
sentences.chinese: 當然，校驗一個戳記所需的時間只是一秒的一小部分。

sentences.english: Postmark is an official mark printed over a postage stamp .
sentences.chinese: 郵戳是印於郵票上的官方戳記。

sentences.english: This is checked based on the timestamp of the last time check.
sentences.chinese: 這是在上一次檢查的時間戳記基礎上被檢查的。
